article.headline: Iona 67, Fairfield 52
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Milan Prodanovic scored 21 points to lead Iona to a 67-52 victory over Fairfield on Friday night. Dexter Gray scored 14 points and Rashon Dwight had 11 points for Iona (7-12, 3-4 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Anthony Johnson had 11 points and Warren Edney 10 for Fairfield (5-12, 3-4). Prodanovic shot 8-for-14 from the field and 5-for-10 from the 3-point range, scoring 16 points in the second half. The Gaels led by as much as 20 points in the second half after Stags coach Ed Cooley was called for double technical fouls and ejected. Gray scored all his points in the first half. Prodanovic shot 4-for-5 from beyond the 3-point line in the second half for the Gaels.
